snippet: As expected, Alabama topped the first rankings. But below the Tide were some unexpected outcomes, and there are plenty of key tests remaining to further scramble the title picture.
abstract: Analysis; Bowl Championship Series releases its first rankings of college football season with Alabama in No. 1 spot, as expected; also on list are some unexpected outcomes, and plenty of key tests remaining to further scramble the title picture; rankings mean little this early in the season, but provide fodder for sports radio and fans.
lead_paragraph: As expected, Alabama topped the first rankings. But below the Tide were some unexpected outcomes, and there are plenty of key tests remaining to further scramble the title picture.

headline.seo: First B.C.S. Rankings Provide Buzz but Little Else
